        <div class="card-body">
          <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-12">
              <div class="container">
                <h1 class="mb-5 text-center"><img src="images/rat.webp" alt="Logo" class="logo me-3"> - Reduced
                  Astrometry Tool (R.A.T.)</h1>
                <section class="mb-5">
                  <h3>General Description</h3>
                  <p>The <strong>Reduced Astrometry Tool (R.A.T.)</strong> allows generating astrometry of astrophotos using the
                    <code><a href="https://astrometry.net/" target="_blank" class="text-decoration-none">Astrometry.net</a></code> engine,
                    specifically through
                    <code><a href="https://manpages.debian.org/testing/astrometry.net/solve-field.1.en.html" target="_blank" class="text-decoration-none">solve-field</a></code>
                    and
                    <code><a href="https://manpages.debian.org/testing/astrometry.net/plot-constellations.1.en.html" target="_blank" class="text-decoration-none">plot-constellations</a></code>.
                    Its main objective is to facilitate obtaining astrometry quickly and customizably, ideal for sharing on social media or saving as a visual record.
                  </p>
                  <p><strong>Note:</strong> This tool is not intended for scientific or professional use. For that, it is recommended to use <a href="https://nova.astrometry.net" target="_blank"
                      class="text-decoration-none">nova.astrometry.net</a>, which offers greater detail, precision, and persistent storage.</p>
                  <p>If you find any errors, have suggestions, or wish to collaborate, write to:
                    <strong>[mail]</strong>
                  </p>
                </section>
                <section class="mb-5">
                  <h3>Main Features</h3>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Supported formats: <code>.jpg</code>, <code>.jpeg</code> and <code>.png</code></li>
                    <li>Maximum size per image: <strong>25 MB</strong></li>
                    <li>Results customization: font size, number of stars, RA and Dec grid</li>
                    <li>Customizable watermark</li>
                    <li>Temporary storage of original and processed image</li>
                  </ul>
                </section>
                <section class="mb-5">
                  <h3>User Guide</h3>
                  <p>Usage is very simple. Here are the steps:</p>
                  <h5>Step 1: Image Upload</h5>
                  <p>Select the image you want to process. A thumbnail with its information will be displayed.</p>
                  <div><img src="images/docs/upload.png" class="img-fluid border border-1 border-secondary mb-4"></div>
                  <h5>Step 2: Space Elements Options (Star Settings)</h5>
                  <ul>
                    <li><strong>Font Size:</strong> Text size for element labels</li>
                    <li><strong>Chart Constellations:</strong> Draws constellation lines</li>
                    <li><strong>Plot NGC Catalog:</strong> Shows objects like clusters, nebulae, galaxies</li>
                    <li><strong>Plot N Brightest Star:</strong> Shows the N brightest stars</li>
                    <li><strong>Plot Named Bright Star:</strong> Adds common names to stars</li>
                  </ul>
                  <div><img src="images/docs/starSetting.png" class="img-fluid border border-1 border-secondary mb-4">
                  </div>
                  <h5>Step 3: Grid Settings</h5>
                  <ul>
                    <li><strong>Plot RA,Dec Grid:</strong> Activates the grid</li>
                    <li><strong>Grid Spacing:</strong> Spacing in arcseconds</li>
                    <li><strong>Grid Color:</strong> Color of grid lines</li>
                  </ul>
                  <div><img src="images/docs/gridSettings.PNG" class="img-fluid border border-1 border-secondary mb-4">
                  </div>

                  <h5>Step 4: Copyright Text (Other Options)</h5>
                  <ul>
                    <li><strong>Copyright Text:</strong> Text for watermark</li>
                    <li><strong>Text Position:</strong> Location in cardinal points</li>
                    <li><strong>Text Color:</strong> Text color (should contrast)</li>
                    <li><strong>Font Size:</strong> Font size</li>
                    <li><strong>Opacity:</strong> Opacity (100% = opaque, 0% = transparent)</li>
                  </ul>
                  <div><img src="images/docs/copyrightText.PNG"
                      class="img-fluid border border-1 border-secondary h-50 mb-4"></div>
                  <h5>Step 5: Process Image</h5>
                  <p>Click on <strong>Upload Image</strong>. The button changes according to the process status:</p>
                  <div>
                    <img src="images/docs/uploadingButton.PNG" class="img-fluid border border-1 border-secondary mb-4">
                    <img src="images/docs/ProcessingButton.PNG" class="img-fluid border border-1 border-secondary mb-4">
                  </div>
                  <h5>Step 6: Results</h5>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Processed image (click to view at full resolution)</li>
                    <li><strong>Object Information:</strong> Position and list of identified objects</li>
                    <li><strong>System Log:</strong> Processing log</li>
                    <li><strong>EXIF Data:</strong> Technical image data</li>
                  </ul>
                  <div><img src="images/docs/visualization.PNG"
                      class="img-fluid border border-1 border-secondary h-50 mb-4"></div>
                  <p><strong>Important:</strong> If the page is closed or reloaded, the process will continue, but the automatic preview will not be shown. The image will appear in the gallery later.</p>
                </section>
                <section>
                  <h3>Final Considerations</h3>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Not a tool for scientific or professional use</li>
                    <li>Images belong to their authors</li>
                    <li>Errors in the process or missing elements may occur</li>
                    <li>Not all existing stellar catalogs are included</li>
                  </ul>
                </section>
